<|startoftext|>Dish: greek rice pilaf
Directions: in a large bowl combine 2 cups flour , yeast , sugar , salt and water , and stir until the dough has formed a ball
transfer the dough to a lightly floured surface and knead the dough for a couple of minutes until it has pulled back from the sides of the bowl
heat the oil over medium heat and add the rice flour and stirring constantly , until the oil begins to bubble and the rice just starts to crisp , about 15 minutes
remove from heat and then cover and place in a warm place for about 8 hours , turning the dough occasionally , until the rice has been doubled in size again
while the cooking process , cover your oven pot and bring to a boil , and allow to simmer for 10 minutes
remove the pancake from the oven and allow to cool
the liquid in the pot should be mostly absorbed by the pancake , and any extra water should be collected
return the pancake to the pot , and remove from heat , add the cream and set the oven to the hot water level
pour into a lightly oiled baking dish , add the butter and stir to blend
pour the batter into the oven pot and bake until the internal temperature reaches 220-250f
you may also do this in a larger serving size but this is not recommended'<|endoftext|>
<|startoftext|>Dish: greek rice pilaf  sopapelle
Directions: in a large pot cover the rice with water and cover with salt , bring to a boil
once rice is soft , add oil , cook rice for a couple of minutes and add 1 / 2 cup of the flour
cover with lid and turn heat off , let it sit on the water for a few minutes , add the rest of the flour and let it cook in oven until the mixture is soft and thickens a bit
remove lid on the pot , add a couple more tablespoons of water in the water then turn the heat off and cover with a lid and allow to steam for about 20 minutes , or until cooked , adding a little more water as you do it
once cooked , remove rice and add the remaining 1 and 1 / 2 cups of flour and stir
let it sit for 10 minutes and add the grated cheese stirring until it forms a nice fluffy sauce
season the sauce with salt and pepper
serve over hot rice'<|endoftext|>
